from django.core.urlresolvers import reverse
from django.db import models
from django.contrib.auth.models import User


# Company
#    Name
#    Notes

class Company(models.Model):
    name = models.CharField(max_length=100, unique=True)
    notes = models.TextField(null=True, blank=True)

    def __unicode__(self):
        return self.name

    def get_absolute_url(self):
        return reverse('company-detail', kwargs={'pk': self.pk})


# Manager
#    Name
#    User *
#    Phone
#    Company *

class Manager(models.Model):
    name = models.CharField(max_length=100, unique=True)
    phone = models.CharField(max_length=100, null=True, blank=True)
    company = models.ForeignKey(Company)
    user = models.ForeignKey(User, null=True)

    def __unicode__(self):
        return self.name

    def get_absolute_url(self):
        return reverse('manager-detail', kwargs={'pk': self.pk})

    def as_row(self):
        return [self.pk, self.name, self.company, self.user.email, self.phone, self.user]

    @staticmethod
    def labels():
        return ['ID', 'Name', 'Company', 'Email', 'Phone', 'User']

    def values(self):
        return zip(Manager.labels(), self.as_row())


# Opening
#   Title
#   Description
#   Skill Analysis
#   Manager
#   Skills *

class Opening(models.Model):
    title          = models.CharField (max_length=100)
    description    = models.TextField (null=True, blank=True)
    skill_analysis = models.TextField (null=True, blank=True)
    is_template    = models.BooleanField(default=False)
    manager        = models.ForeignKey(Manager)

    def __unicode__(self):
            return self.title

    def get_absolute_url(self):
        return reverse('opening-detail', kwargs={'pk': self.pk})

    def fields(self):
        return zip(
            ['Job Title', 'Job Description'],
            ['title', 'description'],
            [self.title, self.description],
        )


# Session
#    Name

class Session(models.Model):
    name = models.CharField(max_length=100)
    opening = models.ForeignKey(Opening)


# Skill
#   Type (Performance/Tech)
#   Title
#   Priority
#   Opening
#   Questions *

class Skill(models.Model):
    name        = models.CharField (max_length=100)
    is_performance_skill = models.BooleanField(default=True)
    priority    = models.IntegerField(default=1)
    opening     = models.ForeignKey(Opening, null=True, blank=True)
    definition  = models.TextField(null=True, blank=True)

    def __unicode__(self):
        return self.name

    def get_absolute_url(self):
        return reverse('skill-detail', kwargs={'pk': self.pk})


# Question
#   QuestionText
#   Selected
#   Skill

class Question(models.Model):
    text       = models.TextField ()
    selected   = models.BooleanField(default=True)
    skill      = models.ForeignKey(Skill)


# Interviewer
#    Company
#    Opening
#    Phone
#    User
#    Questions *

class Interviewer(models.Model):
